Clean slate confirmed. Here's the complete blueprint:

Final Project Structure
SWYM/
├── index.html
├── css/
│   └── style.css
└── js/
    ├── data.js
    ├── store.js
    └── app.js
File-by-File Breakdown
js/data.js
Purpose: Static product catalog. Pure data, zero logic.

PRODUCTS[] — 16 items across 4 categories
  Each product:
    id, name, brand, category
    price, originalPrice
    imageUrl, description, tags[]
    inStock, rating, reviewCount
Categories: Tops · Bottoms · Shoes · Accessories

js/store.js
Purpose: All localStorage reads/writes + wishlist business logic.

Helpers
  generateId()          → unique ID string
  now()                 → ISO timestamp
Read/Write
  getWishlists()        → reads localStorage, returns array
  saveWishlists(lists)  → writes array to localStorage
  getWishlistById(id)   → finds one list by id
Wishlist CRUD
  createWishlist(name)          → new list, auto-sets isDefault if first
  deleteWishlist(id)            → removes; promotes next default if needed
  renameWishlist(id, name)
  setDefaultWishlist(id)        → sets one list as default, clears others
  getDefaultWishlist()          → returns isDefault list or first
Item CRUD
  addItemToWishlist(listId, productId)     → adds with addedAt/note/priority
  removeItemFromWishlist(listId, productId)
  updateItem(listId, productId, patch)     → edit note or priority
  getListsContainingProduct(productId)     → returns array of list IDs
Merge
  previewMerge(idA, idB)        → returns stats (no side effects)
    { listA, listB, onlyInA[], onlyInB[], inBoth[],
      totalUnique, duplicatesResolved }
  mergeWishlists(idA, idB, mode, newListName?)
    → builds combinedMap (dedup by productId)
    → tiebreaker: keep item with earlier addedAt
    → merge notes if both non-empty
    → sort result by addedAt ascending
    → mode "into_a"   → writes into listA
    → mode "new_list" → creates new list
    → returns { targetListId, duplicatesResolved }
css/style.css
Purpose: Full design system, zero JS dependency.

Tokens (CSS custom props)
  --primary, --primary-light, --primary-dark
  --surface, --surface-2, --bg
  --text, --text-muted, --border
  --success, --warning, --danger
  --radius, --shadow, --transition
Base
  Reset, Inter font, body defaults, scrollbar styling
Layout
  .navbar (fixed top, glass blur)
  .view-container (page wrapper)
  .product-grid (CSS Grid, responsive)
Components
  .product-card          → image, info, heart button
  .heart-btn             → ♡/♥ toggle with pulse animation
  .wishlist-card         → list preview card
  .wishlist-detail       → item rows with note/priority
  .badge (priority)      → color-coded high/med/low
Modals
  .modal-overlay         → backdrop blur
  .modal                 → card with slide-up animation
  .merge-modal           → step 1: select, step 2: preview, step 3: confirm
Utility
  .toast                 → slide-in from bottom-right
  .empty-state           → illustration + CTA
  .tag-pill              → filter category pills
  .dropdown-menu         → add-to-list dropdown
  .btn, .btn-primary, .btn-ghost, .btn-danger
Dark mode
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) → swaps all tokens
index.html
Purpose: Shell, nav, all view containers, script/style loading.

<head>
  Google Fonts (Inter)
  style.css
<body>
  <nav>
    Logo | "Shop" link | "My Wishlists" link (with item count badge)
    Dark mode toggle button
  <main id="app">
    <!-- Router injects one of these at a time -->
    #view-shop
      Search bar
      Category filter pills (All / Tops / Bottoms / Shoes / Accessories)
      Sort dropdown (Featured / Price ↑ / Price ↓ / Top Rated)
      #product-grid  ← cards rendered by JS
    #view-wishlists
      "My Wishlists" header + [New List] + [Merge Lists] buttons
      #wishlists-grid ← list cards rendered by JS
    #view-wishlist-detail
      Back link, editable list name, item count
      #items-list ← item rows rendered by JS
    #view-merge
      (rendered as modal overlay on top of wishlists view)
      Step 1: Select List A + List B dropdowns
      Step 2: Preview stats + grouped product thumbnails
      Step 3: Mode radio (into_a / new_list) + new name input
      Step 4: [Confirm Merge] button
  data.js → store.js → app.js  (load order matters)
js/app.js
Purpose: Router + all view renderers + all event handlers.

Router
  hashchange listener
  navigate(hash) helper
  init() → reads hash, renders correct view
View: Shop
  renderShop()
    → filters PRODUCTS by search + category
    → sorts by selected sort
    → renderProductGrid(filtered)
  renderProductCard(product)
    → builds card HTML
    → heart button state: checks getListsContainingProduct(id)
    → "Add to Wishlist" dropdown (lists checkboxes)
  Events
    search input → debounced re-render
    category pills → active toggle + re-render
    sort select → re-render
    heart btn click → show add-dropdown or toggle off
    add-to-list checkbox → addItemToWishlist / removeItemFromWishlist
View: Wishlists
  renderWishlists()
    → renderWishlistCard(list) for each
    → empty state if none
  Events
    [New List] → prompt modal → createWishlist → re-render
    [Merge Lists] → openMergeModal() (disabled if < 2 lists)
    Rename → inline edit
    Delete → confirm → deleteWishlist → re-render
    Set Default → setDefaultWishlist → re-render
    Card click → navigate to #wishlist/:id
View: Wishlist Detail
  renderWishlistDetail(id)
    → renderItemRow(item, product) for each item in list
    → empty state if no items
  Events
    Back → navigate('#wishlists')
    Note input → updateItem (debounced)
    Priority badge click → cycle high→medium→low→high → updateItem
    Remove btn → removeItemFromWishlist → re-render row
View: Merge Modal
  openMergeModal()
  Step 1 — Select
    Render List A dropdown (all lists)
    Render List B dropdown (all lists)        ← BUG #2 here (no exclusion filter)
    On A change → re-render B options, call previewMerge if both selected
    On B change → call previewMerge if both selected
  Step 2 — Preview  (auto-updates on selection)
    Show: totalUnique · duplicatesResolved
    Grouped thumbnails: Only in A | In Both | Only in B
  Step 3 — Mode
    Radio: "Merge into [List A name]" vs "Create new list"
    New list name input (shown only if new_list selected)
  [Confirm Merge] → mergeWishlists → toast → close modal → navigate to result
Toast system
  showToast(message, type)   → creates, appends, auto-removes after 3s
Dark mode toggle
  toggles class on <html>, saves preference to localStorage
Sequence Diagram — Merge Flow
User clicks [Merge Lists]
  → openMergeModal()
  → User picks List A
  → User picks List B  (BUG: same list selectable)
  → previewMerge(A, B) called → shows stats
  → User picks mode (into_a or new_list)
  → User clicks [Confirm]
  → mergeWishlists(A, B, mode)  (BUG: wrong tiebreaker direction)
  → showToast("Merged! X duplicates resolved")
  → navigate to merged list

Build Order
Step	File	Say
1	js/data.js	"build step 1"
2	js/store.js	"build step 2"
3	css/style.css	"build step 3"
4	index.html	"build step 4"
5	js/app.js	"build step 5"
6	Catch & fix mistakes	"resolve mistakes"
7	Deploy to GitHub Pages	"deploy"



